# Markup classes (PHP, jQuery, React)

## Customizer controls

- **Outermost wrapper** of the control UI: **`onepress-{feature}-control`** (matches SCSS root in `.cursor/rules/scss-css.mdc`).
- **Children:** use **functional** class names only (no `onepress-` on each child), e.g. `class="inputs"`, `class="toolbar preview"`. PHP / JSX must match the classes assumed in SCSS under that root.
- **Query / mount:** prefer scoping selectors — e.g. `'.onepress-typo-control .inputs'`, or `root.querySelector('.inputs')` when `root` is the control element.

## Legacy / existing controls

- Older markup may still use **BEM-style** inner classes (`__element`). When editing those files, stay consistent with existing strings until refactored.

## Shared rules

- PHP: **`esc_attr()`** for dynamic class fragments.
- React/JSX: same class strings as SCSS; append state classes (`is-active`) on the toggled node.
- jQuery: identical class names to PHP/React for the same control.

## IDs and `name` attributes

- Theme-owned: keep **`onepress-…`** prefixes where useful for uniqueness (settings, host roots). Valid unique `id` in HTML.

## PHP symbols (not CSS)

- **Classes:** `OnePress_{Feature}_Customize_Control`, etc.
- **Functions:** `onepress_{snake_case}`.
- **Customizer `type`:** e.g. `onepress_typography`, `onepress_layout`.

## File layout (Customizer control PHP)

- New controls live under **`inc/customize-controls/{control-name}/{control-name}.php`** with related PHP colocated; **`require_once`** in **`inc/customizer-controls.php`**. See **`customize-controls-php.mdc`**.
